## Common Triggers for Abusive Behavior

| Trigger                          | Description                                                                                 |
|---------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Disagreement with partner        | Conflicts or arguments that escalate due to poor conflict resolution skills                 |
| Unemployment                    | Loss of income and status leading to frustration and attempts to regain control             |
| Financial issues                | Economic stress increasing tension within the relationship                                 |
| Threat of partner leaving       | Fear of abandonment triggering controlling or violent responses                            |
| Anger escalation                | Poor anger management leading to outbursts                                                |
| Humiliation or failure          | External stressors such as job loss or social humiliation contributing to abusive behavior  |
| Jealousy and envy               | Insecurity driving controlling and possessive behaviors                                    |

These triggers interact with underlying motivations for control and learned patterns of violence ([Gluck, 2021](https://www.healthyplace.com/abuse/domestic-violence/causes-of-domestic-violence-domestic-abuse)).

